import os
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, Dense, BatchNormalization
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import load_img, img_to_array
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam
import glob

# Dataset Path
DATASET_PATH = "/kaggle/input/human-faces/Humans"
IMG_SIZE = (64, 64)  # Image size

# Load Image Paths
image_paths = glob.glob(os.path.join(DATASET_PATH, "**", "*.jpg"), recursive=True) + \
              glob.glob(os.path.join(DATASET_PATH, "**", "*.png"), recursive=True)

if len(image_paths) == 0:
    raise ValueError("No images found! Check dataset path.")

# Load & Preprocess Images
def load_images(image_paths, img_size):
    images = []
    for img_path in image_paths:
        img = load_img(img_path, target_size=img_size)  # Resize
        img = img.convert("RGB")  # Convert to RGB
        img = img_to_array(img) / 255.0  # Normalize
        images.append(img)
    return np.array(images)

# Load dataset
x_data = load_images(image_paths, IMG_SIZE)

# Split into training/testing
split_idx = int(0.8 * len(x_data))
x_train, x_test = x_data[:split_idx], x_data[split_idx:]

# Flatten images
img_shape = x_train.shape[1:]  
x_train = x_train.reshape(len(x_train), -1)
x_test = x_test.reshape(len(x_test), -1)
input_dim = x_train.shape[1]  

# Add noise with reduced factor
noise_factor = 0.2  # Reduced from 0.5
x_train_noisy = x_train + noise_factor * np.random.normal(size=x_train.shape)
x_test_noisy = x_test + noise_factor * np.random.normal(size=x_test.shape)
x_train_noisy = np.clip(x_train_noisy, 0., 1.)
x_test_noisy = np.clip(x_test_noisy, 0., 1.)

# Sparse Autoencoder Architecture
input_img = Input(shape=(input_dim,))
In[6]:
# Encoder
encoded = Dense(512, activity_regularizer=tf.keras.regularizers.l1(10e-5))(input_img)
encoded = BatchNormalization()(encoded)
encoded = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()(encoded)

encoded = Dense(256)(encoded)
encoded = BatchNormalization()(encoded)
encoded = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()(encoded)

encoded = Dense(128)(encoded)
encoded = BatchNormalization()(encoded)
encoded = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()(encoded)

encoded = Dense(64, activation='relu')(encoded)  # Bottleneck

# Decoder
decoded = Dense(128)(encoded)
decoded = BatchNormalization()(decoded)
decoded = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()(decoded)

decoded = Dense(256)(decoded)
decoded = BatchNormalization()(decoded)
decoded = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()(decoded)

decoded = Dense(512)(decoded)
decoded = BatchNormalization()(decoded)
decoded = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()(decoded)

decoded = Dense(input_dim, activation='sigmoid')(decoded)  # Reconstruct image

# Compile Model
autoencoder = Model(input_img, decoded)
autoencoder.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.0005), loss="mse")  # Using MSE

# Train Autoencoder
autoencoder.fit(
    x_train_noisy, x_train,
    epochs=100,  # Increased for better learning
    batch_size=64,  # Reduced batch size for stability
    shuffle=True,
    validation_data=(x_test_noisy, x_test)
)

# Reconstruct images
decoded_imgs = autoencoder.predict(x_test_noisy)

# Display original, noisy, and reconstructed images
n = 10
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 6))
for i in range(n):
    # Original
    ax = plt.subplot(3, n, i + 1)
    plt.imshow(x_test[i].reshape(img_shape))
    ax.axis("off")

    # Noisy
    ax = plt.subplot(3, n, i + 1 + n)
    plt.imshow(x_test_noisy[i].reshape(img_shape))
    ax.axis("off")

    # Reconstructed
    ax = plt.subplot(3, n, i + 1 + 2 * n)
    plt.imshow(decoded_imgs[i].reshape(img_shape))
    ax.axis("off")

plt.show()
